update

public void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                   File _file,
                   String _newVersion)
            throws Exception
The program is updated if the modified date of the file is not the same as the the version property. Embedded TCL update code is searched depending on the file extension and the TCL update needed parameter PARAM_NEEDED. If for a file extension a line prefix is defined, the line prefix is removed from the TCL update code (and also the mark texts defined with PARAM_MARKSTART and PARAM_MARKEND depends on the line prefix).

Specified by:
update in class AbstractObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_file - reference to the file to update
_newVersion - new version which must be set within the update (or null if the version must not be set).
Throws:
Exception - if update of the program failed
See Also:
PARAM_EXTENSION, PARAM_MARKEND, PARAM_MARKSTART, PARAM_NEEDED
